at is the most resolute course to take. (Surah Al 'Imran: 186)
\par }\pard \s15\qj \fi567\li0\ri170\sl-320\slmult0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin170\lin0\itap0 {\f0\fs22\lang2057\langfe1055\langnp2057\insrsid4216250\charrsid881378 
\par In the above verse, God makes it clear that the lies and slander which appeared evil to the believers were, in actuality, good. In another verse, God relates this fact with another example that took place in the time of the Prophet (saas): 
\par 
\par }\pard \s15\qj \li567\ri170\sl-320\slmult0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin170\lin567\itap0\pararsid881378 {\b\f0\fs22\lang2057\langfe1055\langnp2057\insrsid4216250\charrsid881378 
There is a group of you who propagated the lie. Do not suppose it to be bad for you; rather it is good for you. Every one of them will incur the evil he has earned and the one who took it on himself to ampl
ify it will receive a terrible punishment. (Surat an-Nur: 11)
\par }\pard \s15\qj \fi567\li0\ri170\sl-320\slmult0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin170\lin0\itap0 {\f0\fs22\lang2057\langfe1055\langnp2057\insrsid4216250\charrsid881378 
\par Effectively, such circumstances encountered by believers in the past were the tactics employed by the disbelievers to deter and dissuade them from adhering to the tenets of Islam. Yet, the beli
evers always remained steadfast, assured of the fact that these wicked attempts would ultimately turn out beneficially for them, and their cause would prevail in the end. That is why they responded to such slander and verbal attacks with moderation and wi
s
dom; not for a moment did they forget that patience and putting one's trust in God would lead them to success. They were aware that, as the Prophet (saas) said, "whoever remains patient, God will make him patient. Nobody can be given a blessing better and
 greater than patience." (Bukhari)
\par As is in these examples from the past, it is essential for believers of today to submit themselves to the destiny created by God, and to put their faith in the truth that everything develops in accord with a divine purpose
. A believer who lives by these principles will also attain the greatest rewards possible in this world. Because, God promises to help His servants who put their trust in Him, and assures them that they will }{
\f0\fs22\lang2057\langfe1055\langnp2057\insrsid12868698 never }{\f0\fs22\lang2057\langfe1055\langnp2057\insrsid4216250\charrsid881378 find themselves without "a way out": 
\par 
\par }\pard \s15\qj \li567\ri170\sl-320\slmult0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin170\lin567\itap0\pararsid881378 {\b\f0\fs22\lang2057\langfe1055\langnp2057\insrsid4216250\charrsid881378 
If God helps you, no one can vanquish you. If He forsakes you, who can help you after that? So the believers should put their trust in God. (Surah Al 'Imran: 160)
\par }\pard \s15\qj \fi567\li0\ri170\sl-320\slmult0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin170\lin0\itap0 {\f0\fs22\lang2057\langfe1055\langnp2057\insrsid4216250\charrsid881378 
