hile it leads astray into further disbelief those who fail to appreciate the good. Meanwhile, as well as distinguishing the good from evil, these events served to nullify the efforts of the disbelievers. In Surat al-Ahzab, that the disbelievers failed to 
attain success but only returned in rage and deeper hatred, is stated as follows:
